This paper deals with the training dynamics of deep neural networks, specifically in the context of regularization. The paper discusses the behavior of networks with different architectures and activation functions, and their stability under perturbations. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures (cs.DS) as the paper deals with the mathematical and computational aspects of training deep neural networks.
